article.headline: Traore heats up, sparks Boilermakers to beat Illini
article.linkText: Traore heats up, sparks Boilermakers to beat Illini
article.story:
INDIANAPOLIS (AP) -- Lindsay Wisdom-Hylton had 15 points and 
three blocks and Aya Traore added 14 points and five assists to 
lead Purdue (No. 11 ESPN/USA Today, No. 14 AP) to a 68-57 victory over Illinois in the Big Ten 
tournament quarterfinals on Friday night at Conseco Fieldhouse.

Erin Lawless scored 12 points and Katie Gearlds added 12 points 
and five assists for the Boilermakers, who won their second
straight.

Janelle Hughes and Erin Wigley each scored 13 points for
Illinois (15-14), which had won three of their final five games
after an eight-game losing streak.

Purdue (23-5) trailed 36-35 with 15:26 to play before Traore
took control. She made four baskets in just over two minutes to
give the Boilermakers the lead for good.

Purdue suspended backup point guard Cherelle George indefinitely
this week, but the Boilermakers committed just five turnovers.

Gearlds, Purdue's leading scorer and a first-team All-Big Ten
selection, shot 4-for-14 from the field and 1-for-3 from 3-point
range. She struggled in the regular season game aganst Illinois as
well, shooting 4-for-14 in a 57-53 victory in Champaign, Ill.

Hughes scored the first eight points of the game, but the Illini
went cold the rest of the half. Purdue made 9-of-11 shots during a
21-8 run that gave the Boilermakers a 25-16 lead. The Boilermakers
forced 14 turnovers in the first half to take a 29-22 lead at the
break.

Illinois outrebounded Purdue 38-21, but turned the ball over 19
times and allowed the Boilermakers to shoot 49 percent from the
field.
